<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="423" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,474,404,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">Comparative diagnosis</emphasis>
. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Tobias" authorityName="Tobias" box="[827,1030,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Wroughtonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[827,948,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">H. sibirica</emphasis>
Tobias
</taxonomicName>
but differs by having a lamelliform elongate areola on the propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[546,613,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,700,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[340,1247,700,1874]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Helcon sulcatus sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, fore wing; B, hind wing; C, mesosoma, lateral aspect; D, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; E, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; F, habitus, lateral aspect; G, head, lateral aspect; H, head, dorsal aspect; I, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827534/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
F; without such areola in 
<taxonomicName box="[896,1015,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Wroughtonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[896,1015,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">H. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1030,1107,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1460,1482]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,339,1436]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[340,1247,339,1436]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 11. Wroughtonia brachygena sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, wings; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, propodeum, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; D, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; E, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect; F, habitus, lateral aspect; G, head, lateral aspect; H, head, dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827548/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
F) and the frontal depression, first and second metasomal tergites are largely smooth (
<figureCitation box="[793,862,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1897,1919]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,700,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[340,1247,700,1874]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Helcon sulcatus sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, fore wing; B, hind wing; C, mesosoma, lateral aspect; D, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; E, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; F, habitus, lateral aspect; G, head, lateral aspect; H, head, dorsal aspect; I, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827534/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
C, I); at least partly sculptured in 
<taxonomicName box="[1252,1375,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Wroughtonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis box="[1252,1375,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">H. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1460,1482]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,339,1436]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[340,1247,339,1436]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 11. Wroughtonia brachygena sp. nov., ♀, holotype. A, wings; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, propodeum, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; D, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; E, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect; F, habitus, lateral aspect; G, head, lateral aspect; H, head, dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827548/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
D, I).
</paragraph>
